        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 5:56PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 556 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Grover, or 35 miles northeast of Greeley, moving
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grover, Briggsdale, Keota and Pawnee Buttes.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rain is occurring with this storm and may lead to flooding. Do
not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
